  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into quarters</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679304771498-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679304771498-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679304771498-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679304771498-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1679304771498-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s] </strong>into quarters lengthways, then into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into quarters lengthways, then into small, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679304774991-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679304774991-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679304774991-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679304774991-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679304774991-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>pepper</strong>, <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion</strong> <strong>quarters</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>courgette</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> to a large baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-30 min or until the veg is tender and starting to colour – this is your <strong>chunky roast veg</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (or very finely chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679304778946-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679304778946-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679304778946-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679304778946-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679304778946-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken breast</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ras el hanout</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pan and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once cooked, transfer to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679304781947-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679304781947-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679304781947-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679304781947-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679304781947-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> dried cranberries</strong> finely</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and <strong>remaining ras el hanout </strong>– this is your <strong>spiced stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679304785859-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679304785859-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679304785859-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679304785859-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1679304785859-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped cranberries </strong>and <strong>couscous </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>spiced stock</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cover the bowl, then set aside until all of the stock has been absorbed</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679304788907-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679304788907-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679304788907-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679304788907-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1679304788907-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat, then once hot, add your<strong> flaked almonds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden (watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!)</p><p>Once toasted, chop the <strong>toasted almonds </strong>roughly (be careful they may be hot!)</p><p>Fluff the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>couscous</strong> with a fork, then add your <strong>cider vinegar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>– this is your<strong> jewelled couscous</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679304791702-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679304791702-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679304791702-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679304791702-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1679304791702-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chunky</strong> <strong>roast veg</strong>, <strong>spiced chicken breast </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the <strong>toasted almonds </strong>to the jewelled couscous and give everything a good mix – this is your<strong> chicken breast & roasted veg with jewelled couscous</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> chicken breast & roasted veg with jewelled couscous </strong>topped with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>toasted almonds</strong> and<strong> </strong>enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
